                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/21a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-20T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 20, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>291. On February 18 the President declared the defense of Saudi Arabia vital to
                    the defense of the United States, thus rendering Saudi Arabia eligible to
                    receive Lend-Lease aid.</p>
                <p>Please instruct Jidda to convey this information immediately to King Ibn Saud and
                    to ascertain whether this finding of the President is agreeable to him.</p>
                <p>Jidda should report promptly directly to the Department, in as much as publicity
                    regarding the matter is being withheld pending notification to the King.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
